======================================================================
$ blade create process kill -h
======================================================================
Kill process by process id or process name

Usage:
  blade create process kill

Aliases:
  kill, k

Examples:

# Kill the process that contains the SimpleHTTPServer keyword
blade create process kill --process SimpleHTTPServer

# Kill the Java process
blade create process kill --process-cmd java

# Specifies the semaphore and local port to kill the process
blade c process kill --local-port 8080 --signal 15

# Return success even if the process not found
blade c process kill --process demo --ignore-not-found

Flags:
      --blade-release string     Blade release package，use this flag when the channel is ssh
      --channel string           Select the channel for execution, and you can now select SSH
      --count string             Limit count, 0 means unlimited
      --exclude-process string   Exclude process
  -h, --help                     help for kill
      --ignore-not-found         Ignore process that cannot be found
      --install-path string      install path default /opt/chaosblade，use this flag when the channel is ssh
      --local-port string        Local service ports. Separate multiple ports with commas (,) or connector representing ranges, for example: 80,8000-8080
      --override-blade-release   Override blade release，use this flag when the channel is ssh
      --pid string               pid
      --process string           Process name
      --process-cmd string       Process name in command
      --signal string            Killing process signal, such as 9,15
      --ssh-host string          Use this flag when the channel is ssh
      --ssh-key string           Use this flag when the channel is ssh
      --ssh-key-passphrase       Use this flag when the channel is ssh
      --ssh-port string          Use this flag when the channel is ssh
      --ssh-user string          Use this flag when the channel is ssh
      --timeout string           set timeout for experiment

Global Flags:
  -a, --async             whether to create asynchronously, default is false
  -d, --debug             Set client to DEBUG mode
  -e, --endpoint string   the create result reporting address. It takes effect only when the async value is true and the value is not empty
  -n, --nohup             used to internal async create, no need to config
      --uid string        Set Uid for the experiment, adapt to docker and cri



======================================================================
$ blade create process stop -h
======================================================================
process fake death by process id or process name

Usage:
  blade create process stop

Aliases:
  stop, f

Examples:

# Pause the process that contains the "SimpleHTTPServer" keyword
blade create process stop --process SimpleHTTPServer

# Pause the Java process
blade create process stop --process-cmd java

# Return success even if the process not found
blade create process stop --process demo --ignore-not-found

Flags:
      --blade-release string     Blade release package，use this flag when the channel is ssh
      --channel string           Select the channel for execution, and you can now select SSH
      --count string             Limit count, 0 means unlimited
      --exclude-process string   Exclude process
